[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three dogs and one cat die in north Wales house fires

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three dogs and one cat have died in two separate house fires.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
North Wales Fire and Rescue Service was called to a property in Brynford, near Holywell, Flintshire at 20:00 GMT on Saturday, where two of the dogs died.
One person was treated for smoke inhalation and another went to hospital with shock following the blaze started by a TV electrical fault.
The other animals were killed at a large house near Llandudno Junction, Conwy county, but no-one was hurt.
Crews were called at 22:00 and most of the damage was contained in the utility room, but the cause is not yet known.
